n}\label{I} A= \left( \int_{1 +  rac{1}{r^{1-\varepsilon_1}}}^{\infty} + \int_{1 -  rac{1}{r^{1-\varepsilon_1}}}^{1 +  rac{1}{r^{1-\varepsilon_1}}} + \int_{ rac{1}{r}}^{1 -  rac{1}{r^{1-\varepsilon_1}}} ight) e^{-(x-1)^2 r^2} x^{2a-b- rac{1}{2}} \, dx \end{equation} For the first and third integral, we note that, since then $|x - 1| > r^{\varepsilon_1-1}$, $$ e^{-(x-1)^2 r^2} x^{2a-b- rac{1}{2}} < e^{- rac{r^2}{r^{2-2\varepsilon_1}}} x^{2a-b- rac{1}{2}} =e^{-r^{2\varepsilon_1}} x^{2a-b- rac{1}{2}} $$ and hence, the first integral of \eqref{I} is:  egin{equation}\label{I1} \le \int_{1 +  rac{1}{r^{1-\varepsilon_1}}}^{\infty} e^{-r^{2\varepsilon_1}} x^{2a-b- rac{1}{2}} dx = e^{-r^{2\varepsilon_1}} \left ( \int_{1 +  rac{1}{r^{1-\varepsilon_1}}}^{\infty} x^{2a-b- rac{1}{2}} dx ight ) =O(e^{-r^{2\varepsilon_1}}) \end{equation} Similarly, the third integral of \eqref{I} is $O(e^{-r^{2\varepsilon_1}})$. For the second integral we have:  egin{multline*} \int_{1 -  rac{1}{r^{1-\varepsilon_1}}}^{1 +  rac{1}{r^{1-\varepsilon_1}}} e^{-(x-1)^2 r^2} x^{2a-b- rac{1}{2}} \, dx \le \int_{1 -  rac{1}{r^{1-\varepsilon_1}}}^{1 +  rac{1}{r^{1-\varepsilon_1}}} x^{2a-b- rac{1}{2}} \, dx \ =  rac{ (1 +  rac{1}{r^{1-\varepsilon_1}})^{2a-b+ rac{1}{2}} - (1 -  rac{1}{r^{1-\varepsilon_1}})^{2a-b+ rac{1}{2}}}{2a-b+ rac{1}{2}}. \end{multline*} By the Taylor expansion of $(1+x)^{2a-b+ rac{1}{2}}$ at $x=0,$ we deduce that this is $O(r^{-1+\varepsilon_1}).$ Comparing with \eqref{I1}, we see that this bound dominates as $r 	o \infty.$ Therefore, $A=O(r^{-1+\varepsilon_1})$, which we can apply to \eqref{I0} with $r=\sqrt{y}$, to deduce that  egin{equation}\label{M2b} M_2 \ll  rac{y^{ rac14- rac{b}{2}}e^{y } y^{a- rac{b}{2}+ rac14}y^{- rac12+ rac12 \varepsilon_1}}{\left | \Gamma\left( a + ix ight) ight |}= rac{e^y y^{a-b+ rac12 \varepsilon_1}}{\left | \Gamma\left( a + ix ight) ight |}. \end{equation} To bound $M_1$, we note that, by the series definitions of $I_
u$ and $J_{
u}$, we have $|I_{b-1}\left(2\sqrt{2\pi nt}ight)|=|J_{b-1}\left(2i\sqrt{2\pi nt}ight)|$. This, combined with inequality $|J_{
